args:
Tiana makes a deal with the queen to exchange
her own life for Alex's release. Determined to
protect her friends and people, Tiana unites with
the prince's band to quell Leviathan's wrath.
(I have to reach the surface, whatever\nit takes. Only a little ways to go...)
*pant* *pant* Made it. Now to find my\ndarling and the others!
They're a hardy pair, those two.\nI'm sure they're safe, wherever they are.
I certainly hope so... By the way,\nwhere has Princess Chelle gone?
Thought I saw her head off towards the\nsea by herself. She's been doing that a\nlot lately.
I suspect that she feels a measure of\nresponsibility for what happened.
I'm back, darling! Did you miss me?
Yes! And I've got a doozy of a situation\nthat needs some princely intervention.
The abyssians, a surface invasion,\nand Leviathan...
Wild to imagine all these shenanigans're\nhappenin' beneath the sea while we're\nup here none the wiser.
But happening they are. And the abyssians\nneed my darling's help to keep Leviathan\nfrom laying their city to waste.
I'll do whatever I can. But how are we\ngoing to get to the bottom of the sea?
I couldn't help but overhear your little\nconversation. Come with me, my pets!
Wait, the Gran Fiore?! I thought it went\nbelly-up and sank! How the heck is it here\nnow?!
Salvage work. Now, kindly climb aboard.
Uh, won't we get messed up by that big\nmonster down there again?
Bold of you to imply that I would make\nthe same mistake twice.
Shall we? The stage is set for a most\nbrilliant and exciting undersea ball!
Aaagh! It's back again!\nI'm freakin' out here, Chelle!
Peace. A lady is as good as her word.
Gran Fiore Mark II: Hydrocannon Waltz!
My, are we done already? What a trifle.
You built a freakin' cannon on the Gran\nFiore and you're being that casual about it?
If the ship lacks for something,\nI have but to add it. That's all.
So much for my theory that you were out\nto sea looking for our missing friends.
Whatever led you to that conclusion?
All this time, Princess Psycho was just\nworkin' on a Gran Fiore remodel. Woof.\nGuess it all worked out in the end, though.
Our destination is the Kingdom of the\nDeep, Aquaphos. Full speed ahead!
(Damn it all. How many days has it been?)
(The guards don't ever leave an opening.\nI don't think I can break out of here. I can't\nhope for help, either.)
(Wouldn't be surprised if they started\ntalking about execution at some point.\nI need a plan, and fast.)
Tiana?! What are you doing here?
I made a deal with my motherthe queen.\nYou're free to go, Alex.
You'd arrange for a surface-dweller to\nwalk free? That can't have come cheap.
I told her that when all this is over, I\nwould surrender and come quietly to\nmy own execution.
I awakened Leviathan, ravaged\nmy city, and hurt my people.
I have committed a grave sin as a\npriestess of the abyss. This is the best\nway for me to atone for my crimes.
Like hell it is! You're going to die, Tiana!
Yes. But thinking about you being stuck\ndown here, bereft of hope, hurt me more.
Abyssians can't drown, but I have to\nimagine it feels something like the\nway my heart ached for you.
I'm sorry for getting you wrapped up in\nall of this. But I'm glad I met you both,\nfrom the bottom of my heart.
Will you fight together with me until the\nend?
Alex! I'm so glad you're okay!
No time to celebrate a happy reunion.\nWe need to do something about Leviathan.
Yikes! Even his roar is borderline deadly!
If we're not careful, we'll be blown away.\nCleo, please, do like we talked about!
Leave it to me. Here I go!
I quelled the ambient water mana and\namplified its counterparts. Now attacks\nof all elements should work!
Sorry, but we're gonna need you to behave!
Hrk... Humans. What is your goal?
I am a bearer of the dragonblood,\ncome from the surface.
Leviathan, will you bequeath your\nstrength unto me?
This power is too great even for a dragon\nof my caliber, and you would have me\nentrust it to a weak human like you?
Yes. All these long years, you've done\nnothing but slumber to seal yourself away.
You need no longer suffer in isolation.\nLet me share the burden of your power.
Don't make me laugh.\nYou would buckle under its weight.
I would not, and I will prove it to you.\nAnd it is not just your power I would take.\nI would relieve you of your despair, too.
The gloom of the sea is boundless. You\nwould do naught but drown in the abyss.
On the contrary, Leviathan. I will be the\nlight that guides you back from the brink.
Very well. Then show me your power\nthe power to control my raging seas!
